summary.summary: Activity Levels Update:Reported on Friday, April 18, 2025The amount of acute respiratory illness causing people to seek health care remains at a low level.Nationally, emergency department visits for diagnosed influenza and RSV are low and COVID-19 ED visits are now very low.Nationally, influenza (6.7%), and RSV (2.5%) test positivity decreased. COVID-19 (3.4%) test positivity remained stable.Nationally, wastewater viral activity levels for influenza A and COVID-19 are low, and RSV is very low.COVID-19 predictions for the next two weeks suggest that emergency department visits will remain at a very low level. Influenza epidemic trends were not estimated for the U.S. overall this week. We expect the next update on April 25, 2025.
